Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.47,0:00:07.48,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}In{\i0} Elder Tale, {\i1}a quest is a type of mission.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.18,0:00:10.32,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,There are many types,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.32,0:00:13.37,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,ranging from simply finding missing \Npersons to grand adventures,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.37,0:00:15.49,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,each with its own unique reward.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.42,0:00:18.54,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Experience, gold, items...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.99,0:00:21.49,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Magical knowledge or crafting recipes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.48,0:00:24.57,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,The whistle to summon griffons
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.57,0:00:28.12,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,was one of the completion \Nrewards for a huge quest.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.50,0:02:03.91,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Our warehouse is looking pretty bare...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.91,0:02:06.82,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,We should buy up whatever we can.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.82,0:02:08.67,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Ever since the Apocalypse,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.67,0:02:12.98,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,there are fewer guilds that will \Nleave towns to fight for ingredients.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.26,0:02:16.13,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Fighting in your own body is pretty scary...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.13,0:02:19.04,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,That's why lots of people are switching to crafting,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.04,0:02:21.49,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,so ingredients are becoming harder to find.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.04,0:02:25.12,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,In the race to buy them, the large \Nguilds have an advantage...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.45,0:02:30.94,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,The Roderic Merchant Guild and the Marine \NAgency have absorbed many smaller guilds.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.41,0:02:36.15,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,We may be the third biggest crafting guild,  \Nbut it doesn't mean we can take it easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.75,0:02:39.89,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,We must take full advantage of this chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.22,0:02:41.26,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Chance?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.35,0:02:49.27,Title,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1606,1)}Villain in Glasses
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.92,0:02:47.16,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Villain in Glasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.76,0:02:54.42,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,L-Let me go...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.42,0:02:57.19,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have time to waste here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.19,0:02:59.43,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,You look so relaxed, Henrietta.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.43,0:03:01.07,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,My heart is pounding...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.29,0:03:02.98,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not relaxed...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.98,0:03:05.83,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I'm trying to calm my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.83,0:03:07.87,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Assassins are not tools to help you relax.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.87,0:03:09.58,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going into battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.58,0:03:12.58,SignC,H,0000,0000,0000,,Dragon's Nest
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.99,0:03:11.87,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,I must stay strong!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.28,0:03:20.59,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, sorry for keeping you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.19,0:03:24.85,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,You look pretty scary, Marie...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.30,0:03:24.84,HUD1,K,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7}Karashin \N{\fs20}Race/ Human \NSummoner, Lv. 90 \NShopping Street 8
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.28,0:03:26.10,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.10,0:03:28.18,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,It really has been a while, Karashin.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.18,0:03:32.10,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,I'm told you two have known \None another for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.10,0:03:34.86,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,When we were just starting out, \Nwe went hunting together.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.37,0:03:39.74,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,But once we founded our own guilds, \Nwe both became so busy...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.74,0:03:44.26,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,We both started guilds. But isn't yours \Nhuge, with seven hundred members?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.26,0:03:45.87,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Far bigger than mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.14,0:03:48.02,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Well, there are still larger guilds,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.02,0:03:51.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,like the Marine Agency or the \NRoderic Merchant Guild.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.27,0:03:55.88,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Well? What brings you here today? \NYou had something to ask?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.18,0:03:59.16,Default - italics,M,0000,0000,0000,,That's a businessman's face...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.36,0:04:03.30,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like your help with ingredient stocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.69,0:04:06.52,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Ingredients for our guild to use.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.52,0:04:09.72,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,We're trying to outsource our resource collection.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.15,0:04:14.40,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Specifically, we need young deer \Nmeat, lettuce, tomatoes...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.40,0:04:22.19,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Flour, potatoes, haruharu fish, and grouse meat.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.14,0:04:18.26,Default - italics,K,0000,0000,0000,,Just as I thought, she's here for \Ningredients for Crescent Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.77,0:04:23.18,Default - italics,K,0000,0000,0000,,Once you eat their food, \Nyou can't go back to the old stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.18,0:04:25.95,Default - italics,K,0000,0000,0000,,If I could get all that business for myself...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.95,0:04:27.37,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Ingredients?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.57,0:04:29.32,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,How much and at what price?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.99,0:04:37.44,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.44,0:04:40.34,Default - italics,K,0000,0000,0000,,At that price, it's not a bad deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.79,0:04:41.84,Default - italics,K,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.84,0:04:44.65,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,It's a very good deal for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.04,0:04:49.44,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,But that doesn't mean he can simply \Nagree to whatever is proposed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.44,0:04:50.35,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.53,0:04:53.06,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,They'll try to improve the terms.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.64,0:04:55.77,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, these are for
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.29,0:04:58.65,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Crescent Moon, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.65,0:04:59.71,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.71,0:05:01.80,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,I'm told your business is going well.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.80,0:05:03.11,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.47,0:05:07.11,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Our chefs are pleased everyone \Nenjoys the food so much!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.49,0:05:10.62,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,So are you using a new recipe?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.99,0:05:13.12,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Our chefs are simply that good.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.97,0:05:16.93,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,This is right, isn't it, Shiro?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.93,0:05:18.13,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.13,0:05:19.94,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,I can keep this up...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.24,0:05:21.21,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.68,0:05:25.25,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what happens, just keep smiling.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.60,0:05:26.70,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Smiling?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.70,0:05:29.39,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's the most important thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.77,0:05:34.02,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,As long as you keep smiling, \Nyour partner will handle the rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.51,0:05:40.65,Default - italics,H,0000,0000,0000,,She's going to need some help soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.17,0:05:44.29,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,I can give this serious consideration...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.29,0:05:48.95,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,But have you thought of a partnership \Nwith Shopping Street 8,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.95,0:05:51.21,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,in order to grow your business—
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.21,0:05:52.95,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, Karashin...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.63,0:05:55.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.28,0:05:56.30,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Time?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.30,0:05:58.96,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, our other guests have arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.96,0:06:00.06,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.06,0:06:03.46,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Since I knew you already, \NI slipped you in a bit early.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.71,0:06:07.31,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,But Henrietta says we should \Nreally handle this fairly.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.31,0:06:09.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So... What does all this mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.74,0:06:11.34,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,The Marine Agency,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.34,0:06:14.60,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,as well as the Roderic Merchant \NGuild, will be coming, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.60,0:06:15.98,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,But on to other matters...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.28,0:06:17.03,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Wha—
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.03,0:06:18.96,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean by "other matters"?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.96,0:06:20.55,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Well, investment...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.55,0:06:23.98,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Specifically, selling Crescent Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.78,0:06:28.87,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, why don't we ask Karashin to stay?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.87,0:06:31.85,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Until we have a stable source of ingredients,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.85,0:06:33.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we can't move to the next step.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.32,0:06:36.16,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hold on a second...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.48,0:06:39.51,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,What is the Crescent Moon Alliance thinking?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.51,0:06:41.67,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean by "investment"?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.96,0:06:42.89,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Well—
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.89,0:06:47.59,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,How much is Shopping Street 8 willing to pay
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.59,0:06:50.00,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,for that information?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.29,0:06:54.89,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,We'll agree to the matter we \Nwere discussing just now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.89,0:06:59.40,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,We'll get what you want, in any \Nbulk you want, for this price.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.77,0:07:04.73,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Thirty thousand.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.02,0:07:05.68,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Thirty—
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.31,0:07:08.98,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Fine... Agreed!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.98,0:07:12.70,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,On behalf of Shopping Street 8, \NI accept the contract...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.93,0:07:14.24,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,That's great!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.52,0:07:17.83,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Now we can let him stay for the next part, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.83,0:07:19.71,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Of course... I don't mind at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.41,0:07:28.64,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,What's your tailoring level?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.64,0:07:29.76,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Level 32.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.17,0:07:33.05,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Then you can make level-30 leather armor...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.31,0:07:35.66,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Today, make leather aprons to raise your skill.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.80,0:07:36.76,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.33,0:07:42.85,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Since then, Shiroe has been \Nin touch several times.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.02,0:07:47.14,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,He has many friends now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.14,0:07:51.65,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,He and I are in the same world.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.50,0:07:54.21,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,We're in the same world, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.41,0:07:58.91,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,This is how disgusting the world looks to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.04,0:08:05.25,Default - flashback,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,What is this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.37,0:08:07.25,Default - flashback,To,0000,0000,0000,,Minori!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.58,0:08:08.69,Default - flashback,To,0000,0000,0000,,It's you, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.04,0:08:11.35,Default - flashback,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.25,0:08:13.47,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,That day...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.47,0:08:17.18,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The day reality and{\i0} Elder Tale {\i1}switched places...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.09,0:08:26.29,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,All I could do was cry and pray \Nthat someone would save me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.83,0:08:37.45,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Tohya was already starting to accept it...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.15,0:08:39.87,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Walking through this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.56,0:08:41.52,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Running.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.42,0:08:47.43,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,As though he enjoyed the new \Nexperience more than he feared it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.74,0:08:51.76,Default - flashback,To,0000,0000,0000,,Minori, Minori... Look at this!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.45,0:08:55.45,Default - flashback,To,0000,0000,0000,,We still get our EXP pots!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.83,0:09:01.55,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Every day, we still receive the EXP \Npots we got as a beginner bonus.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.17,0:09:06.72,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,When Tohya learned that, it was \Nnatural that he'd want to see
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.72,0:09:08.27,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,how it would work.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.17,0:09:12.53,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Tohya had started to spur me
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.53,0:09:16.91,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,into feeling up to moving forward a little bit...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.89,0:09:18.84,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.68,0:09:22.20,Default - flashback,GUy,0000,0000,0000,,They ran toward four o'clock!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.20,0:09:23.25,Default - flashback,GUy,0000,0000,0000,,Stop them!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.71,0:09:27.45,Default - flashback,To,0000,0000,0000,,Minori!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.88,0:09:31.99,Default - flashback,M,0000,0000,0000,,Tohya!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.99,0:09:36.09,Default - flashback,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,I told you that I wouldn't kill you if you \Ndropped all your inventory items.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.60,0:09:38.39,Default - flashback,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Everything's so realistic...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.76,0:09:40.60,Default - flashback,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Is this really virtual?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.15,0:09:42.83,Default - flashback,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Well, a game's a game...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.83,0:09:44.37,Default - flashback,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Don't blame me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.37,0:09:46.73,Default - flashback,To,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You jerk!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.89,0:09:56.07,Default - flashback,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,I'm alive?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.78,0:09:59.65,Default - flashback,To,0000,0000,0000,,Minori!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.84,0:10:02.96,Default - flashback,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Tohya!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.35,0:10:10.14,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,"In this world, if something matters, \Nkeep it in the bank."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.93,0:10:14.00,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,I only remembered Shiroe's words
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.00,0:10:16.67,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,after I'd already lost everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.45,0:10:18.51,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,By that time,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.98,0:10:22.83,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,all that remained was the \Ndesire to rely on another.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.82,0:10:26.08,Default - flashback,Weirdo,0000,0000,0000,,What's with you guys?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.08,0:10:27.19,Default - flashback,Weirdo,0000,0000,0000,,You newbies?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.91,0:10:29.52,Default - flashback,Weirdo,0000,0000,0000,,No friends?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.91,0:10:31.52,Default - flashback,Weirdo,0000,0000,0000,,That sucks for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.77,0:10:35.03,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,I would have gone with anyone who offered aid,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.03,0:10:36.61,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,no matter who they were.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.48,0:10:45.11,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,The world around Shiroe is the \None he's earned for himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.29,0:10:50.84,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,All I could do was to weep \Nat my own powerlessness.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.00,0:10:53.86,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,The same way I always have.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.23,0:10:59.00,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I lost everything...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.15,0:11:04.30,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,That's why
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.44,0:11:10.27,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,we don't have the right to be saved
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.54,0:11:12.51,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,by Shiroe.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.99,0:11:22.49,SignC,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Dragon's Nest
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.66,0:11:22.95,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, what have we here?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.95,0:11:27.49,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Two beauties and the young \Nmaster of Shopping Street 8.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.04,0:11:30.29,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Hello!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.29,0:11:32.96,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Marielle, of the Crescent Moon Alliance!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.96,0:11:35.18,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,This is my head clerk...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.18,0:11:36.03,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.03,0:11:38.27,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,No one's had a head clerk for years.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.81,0:11:41.76,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Henrietta. Pleased to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.38,0:11:44.96,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,I'm in charge of our treasury.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.80,0:11:46.64,Default - italics,H,0000,0000,0000,,Now, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.89,0:11:49.67,HUD1,H,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7}Michitaka \N{\fs20}Race/ Human \NMonk, Lv. 90 \NMarine Agency
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.18,0:11:50.27,Default - italics,H,0000,0000,0000,,Michitaka, leader of the Marine Agency.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.67,0:11:54.26,HUD1,H,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7}Roderic \N{\fs20}Race/ People of the Law \NSummoner, Lv. 90 \NRoderic Merchant Guild
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.65,0:11:53.84,Default - italics,H,0000,0000,0000,,Roderic, master of the Roderic Merchant Guild.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.75,0:11:59.28,Default - italics,H,0000,0000,0000,,I need to ensure negotiations with \Nthese two are successful.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.14,0:12:02.78,Default - italics,H,0000,0000,0000,,This is my battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.39,0:12:06.78,Default - italics,H,0000,0000,0000,,If I retreat here, I won't be \Nable to face the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.90,0:12:11.23,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Before I get down to business,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.23,0:12:15.79,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,let me explain why I invited \NShopping Street 8 here first.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.22,0:12:20.38,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,We've asked Shopping Street 8 \Nto provide ingredients for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.67,0:12:24.52,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wait... Does that mean you're \Nworking with Shopping Street 8?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.52,0:12:28.64,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,No, then there would be no need to call us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.97,0:12:30.79,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,You must want something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.49,0:12:32.77,Default - italics,H,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.54,0:12:38.95,Default - italics,H,0000,0000,0000,,Michitaka is a respected leader, \Nbut subtlety isn't his strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.43,0:12:42.78,Default - italics,H,0000,0000,0000,,Roderic appears similar to Shiroe,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.78,0:12:45.53,Default - italics,H,0000,0000,0000,,but he lacks Shiroe's guts.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.85,0:12:48.26,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's right. It's something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.61,0:12:53.90,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,We'd like to extend the same \Noffer to both of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.68,0:12:59.97,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,The only thing we can sell for \Nthe money we require
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.97,0:13:03.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is our new method of food preparation.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.61,0:13:05.59,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, but that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.96,0:13:06.82,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.33,0:13:11.77,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Once they know how, using it is \Nthe simplest thing in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.45,0:13:17.48,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,So, no matter what, we can't let them \Nin on it until after the negotiations.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.93,0:13:21.18,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, but we can't go to them
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.18,0:13:23.75,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,without telling them anything...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.75,0:13:27.11,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,That's one place where we have an advantage.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.65,0:13:29.12,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,An advantage?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.59,0:13:32.91,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Our advantage is that they want profits.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.00,0:13:34.98,Default - italics,H,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.64,0:13:38.36,Default - italics,H,0000,0000,0000,,Crescent Moon is tempting bait.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.12,0:13:41.38,Default - italics,H,0000,0000,0000,,As long as they desire to profit,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.41,0:13:45.88,Default - italics,H,0000,0000,0000,,we maintain the negotiating initiative.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.02,0:13:50.51,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,We have the right to decide \Nwhat information we reveal,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.03,0:13:54.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as well as what we keep hidden.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.51,0:13:58.52,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,However, we cannot lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.08,0:14:03.36,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,But to dangle the bait, while trying \Nto avoid telling them anything...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.82,0:14:07.86,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,If this is to work in the future, \Nwe can't afford to lie now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.63,0:14:13.89,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,I'd better get Akatsuki for a whole week, \Nor this won't be worth it at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.87,0:14:20.25,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,The Crescent Moon Alliance is \Nembarking on a major operation.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.71,0:14:22.20,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,A major operation?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.57,0:14:26.43,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,You could think of it as a challenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.05,0:14:32.76,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,However, we lack the power to \Ndo it completely on our own.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.14,0:14:35.25,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Then you want our help?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.78,0:14:39.81,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I understand... A quest, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.63,0:14:44.80,Default - italics,H,0000,0000,0000,,Good, they misunderstood me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.80,0:14:47.78,Default - italics,H,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not lying, Shiroe!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.17,0:14:52.45,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,So, what kind of support \Nwould you need, Marie?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.73,0:14:55.24,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Before I tell you what we need,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.24,0:14:58.33,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,let me explain how we've organized ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.70,0:15:01.58,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'd like to hear your strategy, at least.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.89,0:15:02.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.41,0:15:07.88,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,The man in charge of our \Nmajor operation is Shiroe.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.44,0:15:11.59,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,The Villain in Glasses is doing this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.32,0:15:13.60,Default - italics,H,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.19,0:15:15.35,Default - flashback,M,0000,0000,0000,,Griffons?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.07,0:15:19.68,Default - flashback,H,0000,0000,0000,,That explains how you traveled to \Nand from Susukino so quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.14,0:15:23.90,Default - flashback,M,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't those summon flutes a reward \Nfor a nigh-impossible raid?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.28,0:15:29.35,Default - flashback,H,0000,0000,0000,,I can understand the Tea Party's \Nstrategist having one.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.72,0:15:32.91,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, so he's behind this.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.38,0:15:35.95,Default - italics,H,0000,0000,0000,,He's more famous than I expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.41,0:15:42.37,Default - italics,H,0000,0000,0000,,Just their knowing that Shiroe is leading \Nthis operation lends weight to my words.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.08,0:15:47.59,Default - italics,H,0000,0000,0000,,The name "Villain in Glasses" isn't just for show.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.79,0:15:50.58,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sick, my lord?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.58,0:15:53.67,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Can you get sick in this world?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.82,0:16:00.27,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Let's move on to the support we're \Nrequesting from each of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.86,0:16:04.37,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,To be blunt, we need money.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.88,0:16:06.26,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,I thought so.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.26,0:16:07.84,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,How much?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.84,0:16:10.03,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,At present, we need
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.42,0:16:13.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,five million gold.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.48,0:16:14.22,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Fi—
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.22,0:16:15.33,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Five million?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.25,0:16:21.79,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,I've never heard of any quest \Nthat costs that much money.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.22,0:16:23.48,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.48,0:16:25.60,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Then The Novasphere Pioneers?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.07,0:16:29.33,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,With the expansion pack in place,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.33,0:16:33.18,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,it would make sense if there were \Nnew legendary-class quests.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.69,0:16:37.34,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Which means the reward for that quest...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.23,0:16:42.18,Default - italics,H,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what it is, it's likely \Nto lead to lots of money.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.02,0:16:45.04,Default - italics,H,0000,0000,0000,,They want to believe that's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.55,0:16:51.07,Default - italics,H,0000,0000,0000,,And when someone wants to believe \Nsomething is true, they usually will.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.81,0:16:56.82,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Try this! It's a new recipe.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.38,0:16:59.68,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,It's made from Roc eggs.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.68,0:17:01.21,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,It's sweet and delicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.21,0:17:02.58,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Pudding?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.97,0:17:04.96,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,It's great!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.63,0:17:08.09,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,This is really Roc eggs?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.09,0:17:12.46,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Rocs are level 85 and above...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.25,0:17:15.36,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,To cook these eggs,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.36,0:17:18.35,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,you'd need a recipe we don't know of, \None that's above level 90.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.54,0:17:22.37,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally, we wouldn't give you \Nnothing in return for the money.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.37,0:17:25.10,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Once the operation is complete,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.10,0:17:28.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we'll give all three of you full \Ndetails about the plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.11,0:17:30.36,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Also...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.77,0:17:33.74,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,We're prepared to ask a scribe to transcribe
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.74,0:17:36.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,copies of all the cookbooks we're currently using,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.66,0:17:40.78,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,as well as the methods we've learned \Nover the course of our challenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.58,0:17:43.14,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.14,0:17:46.59,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,The recipes Crescent Moon is using?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.90,0:17:49.75,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Then there is a special recipe...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.17,0:17:53.52,Default - italics,H,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like we're through the rough part.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.52,0:17:55.73,Default - italics,H,0000,0000,0000,,Now to throw them a life jacket.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.74,0:18:00.64,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Through asset liquidation and \NCrescent Moon's sales,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.64,0:18:02.97,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,we've collected 500,000 gold.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.50,0:18:09.23,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,But asking any single guild to provide \Nthe remaining 4.5 million
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.23,0:18:12.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,would greatly alter the balance of power.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.37,0:18:18.53,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,So why don't we have each guild \Ncontribute 1.5 million?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.94,0:18:21.49,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,That represents around a \Nhundred people's assets...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.31,0:18:24.87,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,The Roderic Merchant Guild \Nagrees to your proposal.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.29,0:18:26.20,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Same here!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.20,0:18:27.83,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Shopping Street 8 does, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.83,0:18:29.17,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.17,0:18:31.84,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,The Marine Agency will provide the funds.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.27,0:18:36.55,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,If you prefer, we could be your sole sponsor.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.00,0:18:38.37,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,That's no fair!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.37,0:18:40.60,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I won't allow you to take all \Nthe profit for yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.03,0:18:44.26,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Let's be civil, everyone... For me, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.68,0:18:50.37,Default,To,0000,0000,0000,,Hear from him again?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.22,0:18:53.32,Default,To,0000,0000,0000,,From Shiroe.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.32,0:18:54.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shh!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.78,0:18:56.77,Default,To,0000,0000,0000,,Listen...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.96,0:18:59.38,Default,To,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't tell you,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.84,0:19:01.85,Default,To,0000,0000,0000,,but I saw him once earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.82,0:19:06.91,Default,To,0000,0000,0000,,But I couldn't ask him for help.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.91,0:19:08.75,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.60,0:19:10.72,Default,To,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.66,0:19:13.77,Default,To,0000,0000,0000,,He's so cool, so kind...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.77,0:19:15.00,Default,To,0000,0000,0000,,He knows everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.23,0:19:17.72,Default,To,0000,0000,0000,,He's just so amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.41,0:19:19.26,Default,To,0000,0000,0000,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.59,0:19:21.22,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.11,0:19:27.51,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,We have no right to ask someone \Nlike him to save us.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.10,0:19:30.51,Default,To,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think I could be like him?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.93,0:19:36.20,Default,To,0000,0000,0000,,Right now, I couldn't ask him to save me...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.24,0:19:41.41,Default,To,0000,0000,0000,,But if I could be like him...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.48,0:19:48.66,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,I'm done for.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.66,0:19:51.42,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,It feels like my HP and MP are at zero...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.96,0:19:53.68,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,I suddenly feel so exhausted.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.55,0:19:55.92,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,This smell...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.38,0:19:57.87,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Akatsuki!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.87,0:20:00.51,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,You aren't smelling me. \NThat's the dessert.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.51,0:20:03.27,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,When you're tired, sweets are the best!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.27,0:20:04.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Meow.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.22,0:20:07.50,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.50,0:20:08.97,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,You all had a tough time, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.97,0:20:10.12,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.50,0:20:12.42,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Shiro asked us to.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.42,0:20:15.22,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,He said you'd be tired when you got back.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.22,0:20:16.57,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,He did?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.03,0:20:18.53,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Where is he, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.83,0:20:20.36,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,I should tell him how it went.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.63,0:20:24.26,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,He's already working on the next job.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.26,0:20:28.87,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,He was certain you'd be able to pull it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.59,0:20:36.38,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,It feels like he planned for everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.02,0:20:40.56,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,There's no beating the Villain in Glasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.29,0:20:47.60,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,We're splitting up for tonight's sparring match.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.60,0:20:49.06,Default,All,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.83,0:20:53.19,Default,Ri,0000,0000,0000,,What has the Crescent Moon \NAlliance invited us to?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.64,0:20:56.26,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,They said they wanted to talk \Nabout the city of Akihabara,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.26,0:20:58.15,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,but the details were vague.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.75,0:21:02.15,Default,Ri,0000,0000,0000,,She once tried and failed to make an alliance
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.15,0:21:04.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,of smaller guilds, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.96,0:21:07.05,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know if they're true,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.05,0:21:09.66,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,but the stories about the guy \Nworking with her bother me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.35,0:21:13.90,Default,Ri,0000,0000,0000,,You mean Log Horizon?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.36,0:21:15.17,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.24,0:21:18.91,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,It's Shiroe, from the Tea Party.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.29,0:21:23.80,SignA,I,0000,0000,0000,,We humbly request your presence \Nat a meeting to determine \NAkihabara's future. \N\NCrescent Moon Alliance \NGuild Master Marielle \NLog Horizon \NGuild Master Shiroe
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.12,0:21:23.80,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,Then does this mean the next \Nraid is canceled, my lord?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.07,0:21:24.75,Default,C,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.16,0:21:27.37,Default,C,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately, the dates overlap.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.95,0:21:30.31,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,Is this conference that important?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.86,0:21:33.08,Default,C,0000,0000,0000,,I'm less interested in the conference itself
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.18,0:21:36.23,Default,C,0000,0000,0000,,than in the one holding it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.14,0:21:44.11,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I'm doing it tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.66,0:21:49.15,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I promised I'd come and save you, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.58,0:21:53.08,SignB,S,0000,0000,0000,,Shiroe
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.27,0:21:52.63,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,So that's okay, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.84,0:21:59.97,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Tohya said he wanted to be like Shiroe.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.99,0:22:04.47,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,He wants to open new paths, like Shiroe.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.94,0:22:08.97,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,That is what he wants!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.03,0:22:13.32,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,And I do, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.88,0:22:29.85,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,It's time, Shiro.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.12,0:22:30.79,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.35,0:22:32.49,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Now it's my turn...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.64,0:22:35.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.88,0:24:10.26,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,At the guild building, twelve masters gather.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.26,0:24:13.05,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,The battle begins, as Shiroe fights weaponless.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.61,0:24:16.97,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,And the new players trapped by Hamelin,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.97,0:24:20.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Minori and Tohya, are about \Nto begin their fight, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.91,0:24:23.17,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,To open the door to hope...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.48,0:24:30.99,Title,Next time,0000,0000,0000,,Round Table Conference
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.86,0:24:25.70,Default,Next time,0000,0000,0000,,Next time: Round Table Conference.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.41,0:24:28.25,Default,Next time,0000,0000,0000,,This is our reality.
